LANN-BRICK is a quiet campsite that welcomes you in a wooded and flowery setting of 1.5 hectares, including delimited pitches for tents and caravans and rental of mobile homes, "Tithome" rental, canvas bungalows and caravans. Our 3 star campsite (Camping Qualité label) offers you a heated swimming pool, a playground for children and adults and a multitude of activities during your vacation stay in Locmariaquer. Near Carnac, Locmariaquer, in Southern Brittany, is located at the entrance of the Gulf of Morbihan, ideal starting point for multiple cruises in this maritime paradise with its many islands: Ile-aux-Moines, Houat islands, Hoedic, Belle-Ile ... Locmariaquer is also a world-famous megalithic site.Many activities are possible: - Fishing - - Tennis, Mini-Golf - Sailing - Diving ... Kayaking in the Gulf of Morbihan of course, but also on the rivers of Auray, Bono, Crac'h. Numerous walks, water sports and cycling. Bicycle rental on site.

Nestled in Locmariaquer on a magnificent site with trees and flowers, this establishment is located a stone's throw from the beaches and the pier for the islands (Ile-aux-Moines, Houat, Hoëdic, Belle-Île). Also 15 minutes from Carnac and the port of St Goustan in Auray, it allows you to discover the many facets of Morbihan on foot, by bike or by boat. Impeccably run by friendly owners, it offers spacious pitches and a wide choice of accommodation (mobile homes, canvas bungalows, tithomes and caravans) to meet all expectations. Its heated swimming pool with paddling pool as well as its numerous outdoor activities or sheltered in its game room (ping-pong, petanque, children's activity area, billiards, table soccer, pinball machine...), will satisfy young and old. Finally, a host of activities and services (theme evenings, night market, wifi, bike rental, snack bar, bar, grocery store) are also available to ensure an absolutely relaxing stay.
